/manchesters-coop-live-boss-not-embarrassed-by-gig-postponements-focus-on-ensuring-consistent-total-power-supply-3750093">组织者坚称他们对推迟“并不感到尴尬”</a> ，而是专注于让场馆恢复正常。然而就在几天后，有消息传出， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/manchester-co-op-live-arena-boss-resigns-after-rows-controversy-and-venue-problems-3750847">新球馆老板加里·罗登在争议中辞职</a>。</p><p>辞职前，罗登因其对草根音乐场所的评论而受到批评，他在评论中表示， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-hit-back-at-manchesters-co-op-live-for-saying-some-grassroots-venues-are-poorly-run-despite-arena-facing-own-major-issues-3749643">英国一些较小的音乐场所“经营不善”</a> ，并驳回了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-case-has-been-made-for-a-1-ticket-levy-on-all-arena-gigs-for-the-survival-of-grassroots-venues-and-artists-3611533">对所有演出场地大小和规模的演出征收 1 英镑门票费的呼吁。多于</a>。</p><p>对此， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-say-manchester-co-op-live-arena-comments-were-disrespectful-and-disingenuous-and-call-on-1-ticket-levy-to-save-uk-talent-pipeline-3749732">音乐场馆信托基金 (MVT) 首席执行官马克·戴维德 (Mark Davyd) 向<em>《NME》</em>表示，他认为罗登的言论“不尊重且不诚实”</a> ，同时也强调了对音乐场所发表此类<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-hit-back-at-manchesters-co-op-live-for-saying-some-grassroots-venues-are-poorly-run-despite-arena-facing-own-major-issues-3749643">“判断错误、不必要和误导性”言论</a>的讽刺意味。一周后，他的场馆被迫推迟开业。</p><p>后来， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-say-manchester-co-op-live-arena-is-a-great-idea-but-urge-them-to-work-in-a-way-that-secures-the-future-of-live-music-3752713">MVT 表示新的 Co-Op Live Arena 是“一个好主意”，但敦促老板们“以确保现场音乐未来的方式开展工作”</a> 。</p><p>其他计划在曼彻斯特 Co-Op Live 演出的乐队包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-black-keys">The Black Keys</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eric-clapton">Eric Clapton</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nicki-minaj">Nicki Minaj</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eagles">Eagles</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pet-shop-boys">Pet Shop Boys</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/liam-gallaghe